<br>
1. We can use magic without having to med. Our songs are not as powerful as casting classes, but the total effect/mana ratio makes it worth it. We can haste, clarity, buff, debuff, heal, mez, charm, invis, snare, slow, zing, levitate, DoT, mana sieve, bind sight, and run faster than any other class out there.<br>
<br>
2. There are very few 40+ bards out there, so our presence in guilds and on raids is generally low. That means less competition for class-specific drops.<br>
<br>
3. It's incredibly fun! Bards are so diverse that our role in a party or raid changes depending on the circumstances. Few or no enchanters? You're crowd control, mana regen, and haste. All casters? You're the tank. All tanks? You're the buffer, healer, and DoT person. You are forced to change your song choices and play style from group to group.<br>
<br>
4. It's hugely challenging. Mages think controlling a pet is tough? Try twisting 3-4 songs while switching instruments at the same time. Carpal tunnel sucks but when your tanks have 1000+ AC and 255 str while being healed, hasted, and damage shielded, it's all worth it.<br>
<br>
5. You're always welcome in groups. Head to Velks or Karnors sometime soon. Bards as chanters are necessary there. Those who hunt there know that a good bard can handle up to 3 mezzed mobs at once and that makes to save a messy CR when adds arrive.<br>
<br>
Whew! Did I write all that? Sheesh. Hope that helps. <p><p align="center">
